com.krobothsoftware.commons.progress

Class ProgressMonitor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.krobothsoftware.commons.progress.ProgressMonitor
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    NullProgressMonitor, SubProgressMonitor

    public class ProgressMonitor
extends Object
    Monitor class for progresses.

    To get a monitor instance, call newInstance(ProgressListener). If Listener is null, it will create a ProgressMonitor

    Each monitor has a set number of ticks. beginTask(String, int). Calling the worked(int) method will increment the tick X number of times. When done, simply call done() Note a Listener may return a cancel request. isCanceled()

    Since:
    SNC 1.0
    See Also:
    SubProgressMonitor
